Interview with the Vampire: The Vampire Chronicles is a 1994 film based on the 1976 novel Interview with the Vampire by Anne Rice. The film was directed by Neil Jordan, and stars Tom Cruise, Brad Pitt, Antonio Banderas,Stephen Rea and Kirsten Dunst

This is such an amazing film and one of my very favorites of all time! I was so anxious to see it when it came out in 1994. There was so much buzz surrounding this long awaited film adaption of Anne RiceÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s famed novel and also surrounded the cast; an A list of popular, talented, young stars entrenched in pop culture. Everything about this media text is so stylish, seductive and thoughtful. The characters are so well portrayed by an amazing cast; lead Cruise as Lestat was so outstandingly evil and captivating in the part. You couldnÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢t youÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢re your eyes off him. Brad Pitt, as Louis was so beautiful, yet so chronically depressed, and torched in this role. Many times in the film he had to reflect LouisÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s eternal despair with mere facial reactions. He pulled it off so well! Antonio Banderas who was just becoming popular at that point in time really captured the old world appeal of the greatly powerful and knowledgeable Armand. Stephen Rea who had just come off starring in another Neil Jordan masterpiece: The Crying Game, made his character Santiago so vindictive and heartless, as a member of the audience you just loved to hate him. And the surprise in a very young and wickedly talented Kirsten Dunst as Claudia who shared so many scenes with big, notable, experienced stars, and equaled their fine performances. The scene where Claudia finally realizes she will never grow up and mature to be a woman and explodes at Lestat and Louis (Cruise and Pitt) was amazing and one of the great many scenes of this film! The sets are incredible and masterfully designed along with a beautifully, haunting musical score. A wonderful film adaption of the epic novel with some wicked twists. One of the great horror films, certainly of the vampire subgenera of all time!

This is a classic piece of media to enjoy just as Halloween approaches. If you love the film, or have not seen it before you will love the extras included in this release. They really help to define the film through the revelations of the cast and crew and are a wonderful tribute to an amazing piece of work. Enjoy for Halloween! Please SEED! Cheers. 

